  "title": "Assistant Quality Manager (Aerospace)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work as a team to create and implement comprehensive quality assurance plans that outline the processes and procedures for ensuring quality throughout the product lifecycle, from design to manufacturing to delivery.</li>\n  <li>Conduct internal and external audits to assess the effectiveness of quality control procedures and identify areas for improvement.</li>\n  <li>When quality issues are identified, work to determine the root cause of the problem, develop corrective actions, and monitor their implementation to ensure they are effective.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that company's products and services meet relevant industry standards and regulations, including standards like NADCAP.</li>\n  <li>Provide training and awareness programs for employees on quality control procedures and best practices.</li>\n  <li>Actively participate in continuous improvement projects to enhance quality and reduce costs.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with suppliers to ensure that their products and services meet the required quality standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Min Degree in Engineering</li>\n  <li>Min 3 years of experience in certifying staff and lead QA activities</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To submit your application, please apply online <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com</strong></a><strong> </strong>or call<strong> </strong><a href=\"tel:+(65)%C2%A06513 5697\"><strong>+(65) 6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p>\n<p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p>\n<p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd<br>\nEA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
